developerResponse: {'reviewId': '5b7bb56f-4577-4bab-a9c5-a55f3a723827', 'userName': 'Keely Hokenson', 'userImage': 'https://play-lh.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUa-ZXwS9VutCmRmT7CWvQX9sdKMWrs9i_yNfsJvEE7AbQ_piJXvw', 'content': "This app has great features for early learning and teachers, specifically during distance learning. review: This app has great features for early learning and teachers, specifically during distance learning. developerResponse: {'reviewId': '50bd548c-e614-4dbf-8081-1b43926a2ddb', 'userName': 'Alex Mason', 'userImage': 'https://play-lh.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIl9XnG2W2ucdt6m00OHt91asALddlK5qW0XiwPpGqAS0HE_QY=mo', 'content': 'I have updated my review. review: I have updated my review. An issue I had with Family Link which is resolved, thanks to a tip from the app author (on a weekend no less). Thank you to them for that. Regarding the app, it is quite simple and both my kids have enjoyed using it. I would say that the default word lists are a little simple for my daughter (7) but for my son (4) its great. review: It's okay. The UK letter forms are good mostly, but the 'rewards' are repetitive, random and a bit boring. It'd be good to be able to track progress. It'd be good to have a side-by-side mode, so kids aren't always tracing the path, but trying to copy. Would be good to be able to see how they do if the line is not constrained to the path of the letter. Feels a little expensive to buy, but I appreciate there are no ads. ¬£1.99 and I wouldn't have hesitated.

developerResponse: {'reviewId': '68571bbb-53a5-4d8f-a46d-89aef010343c', 'userName': 'A Google user', 'userImage': 'https://play-lh.googleusercontent.com/EGemoI2NTXmTsBVtJqk8jxF9rh8ApRWfsIMQSt2uE4OcpQqbFu7f7NbTK05lx80nuSijCz7sc3a277R67g', 'content': "This is one of the best writing apps I have found. It really helps my additional needs (global development delay, learning difficulties) daughter with her emergent writing. She has gone from huge melt downs when trying to write, to asking for this app daily. (And her recall of letters is growing daily) It's easy enough for her to navigate herself, and has various different difficulty settings which has been great as both my daughters are at different levels and have different abilities. You do have to pay to unlock all letters, but I felt (and still do) that it's worth doing so. When you factor in both my girls have it on their tablet, and use it daily ¬£3.84 ( I think it was) is worth it. I very rarely leave reviews on apps, but I honestly feel that this is definitely an app worth having.  More of the same please!", 'score': 5, 'thumbsUpCount': 43, 'reviewCreatedVersion': '2.5.0', 'at': datetime.datetime(2018, 4, 6, 15, 15, 56), 'replyContent': 'Thanks for your great review!', 'repliedAt': datetime.datetime(2018, 4, 7, 2, 25, 51), 'appVersion': '2.5.0'}
review: This is one of the best writing apps I have found. It really helps my additional needs (global development delay, learning difficulties) daughter with her emergent writing. She has gone from huge melt downs when trying to write, to asking for this app daily. (And her recall of letters is growing daily) It's easy enough for her to navigate herself, and has various different difficulty settings which has been great as both my daughters are at different levels and have different abilities. You do have to pay to unlock all letters, but I felt (and still do) that it's worth doing so. When you factor in both my girls have it on their tablet, and use it daily ¬£3.84 ( I think it was) is worth it. I very rarely leave reviews on apps, but I honestly feel that this is definitely an app worth having.  More of the same please!

I bit the bullet and decided to buy this app to help them with their phonics.   One gripe - in the UK we say 'zed- not blooming 'zee'!!!  I love the reward of playing with the finished letter. developerResponse: {'reviewId': 'f75b5cbc-6786-41f5-a08b-ae91571a53e9', 'userName': 'A Google user', 'userImage': 'https://play-lh.googleusercontent.com/EGemoI2NTXmTsBVtJqk8jxF9rh8ApRWfsIMQSt2uE4OcpQqbFu7f7NbTK05lx80nuSijCz7sc3a277R67g', 'content': 'I finally got refunded from the Handwriting Without Tears app, which never worked, and used that to buy the full version of this app!  I am not a huge fan of using apps for my kids, but with handwriting being such a struggle, this is a fun, low-pressure way for my oldest to practice the letters without me constantly correcting him.  I tweaked the settings to make it as low-key as possible.  It doesn\'t have to show crazy pictures, it can just look like a pen.  The 5-star practice mode is great for reinforcing the mechanics of each letter and number, and it can be customized by letter size, difficulty, etc.  It is well worth the few dollars it costs to unlock the whole game, but you get a decent amount of letters to preview, so try it first!!  My only suggestion would be to disable all the "play" after a letter or number is drawn.  I thought there was a way to do that but can\'t seem to find it.  Also, a way to disable the crazy animation and games globally rather than for each of the five star levels would be wonderful too!', 'score': 5, 'thumbsUpCount': 20, 'reviewCreatedVersion': '2.3.5', 'at': datetime.datetime(2017, 3, 13, 13, 29, 42), 'replyContent': None, 'repliedAt': None, 'appVersion': '2.3.5'}
review: I finally got refunded from the Handwriting Without Tears app, which never worked, and used that to buy the full version of this app!  I am not a huge fan of using apps for my kids, but with handwriting being such a struggle, this is a fun, low-pressure way for my oldest to practice the letters without me constantly correcting him.  I tweaked the settings to make it as low-key as possible.  It doesn't have to show crazy pictures, it can just look like a pen.  The 5-star practice mode is great for reinforcing the mechanics of each letter and number, and it can be customized by letter size, difficulty, etc.  It is well worth the few dollars it costs to unlock the whole game, but you get a decent amount of letters to preview, so try it first!!  My only suggestion would be to disable all the "play" after a letter or number is drawn.  I thought there was a way to do that but can't seem to find it.  Also, a way to disable the crazy animation and games globally rather than for each of the five star levels would be wonderful too!
